Andropogoneae Species

Michelle C. Stitzer

Andropogon gerardi

Photo by Brett Whaley, licensed under CC BY 2.0

The assembly is allelic, and the genome is hexaploid. It has a haploid genome size of 2300 Mb, and has 30 haploid chromosomes.

Metaphase chromosomes of Andropogon gerardi, scale bar 10 m

Species herbarium records

Herbarium records of Andropogon gerardi from AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022 are plotted with black points, The sampled individual this genome was generated from is shown in a colored point. The green background shows the biogeographic ranges of all Andropogoneae species in AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022.

Figure 2 from the main text, with Andropogon gerardi highlighted with colored points.

Dotplot of Andropogon gerardi vs.Paspalum vaginatum.

Like dotplots shown in Figure 3 of the main text, this shows syntenic blocks in Andropogon gerardi along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum on the x-axis. As Andropogon gerardi is a hexaploid with an allelic, assembly, we expect 6 paths for any x-axis position.

Fractionation of Andropogon gerardi

Like plots shown in Figure 4 of the main text, this shows proportion of retained genes in Andropogon gerardi along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum chromosomes on the x-axis. As Andropogon gerardi is a hexaploid with an allelic, assembly, we expect 6 lines, two for each subgenome.
